Tiger Vision
March 19, 2019 at 1:47 PM Â·

Attention Tiger Fans!

We need your help. As you have seen, there are many of our fellow Iowans who are being heavily affected by the flooding in SW Iowa. Tiger Vision is partnering with I Saw the Sign and Western Iowa Networks to send much needed supplies to Mills County, Iowa.

They are in DESPERATE need of the following items:
1. Money to be donated to individual town flood funds
2. Toothbrushes/toothpaste
3. Shampoo/conditioner
4. Laundry soap
5. Body soap
6. Dish soap
7. Cases of water
9. Masks and rubber gloves
10. Mold/mildew cleaner
11. Household brooms/push brooms
12. Bleach and mops
13. Hand sanitizer and wipes

You may drop items off in the Tiger Vision room at Carroll High school. You can also bring a cash donation that will be given as well. The items & money will be transported to Mills County this weekend.

Thank you so much in advance for your generous donations!

**Photo taken of Pacific Junction, right outside of Glenwood.**

PLEASE SHARE AND SPREAD THE WORD!!!!

Denison Bulletin & Review
October 31, 2018 at 1:24 AM Â·

Ar-We-Va saw its volleyball season end on Tuesday night with a 3-1 loss to 11th-ranked Gladbrook-Reinbeck in the Class 1A, Region 3 final at Boone High School.

Gladbrook-Reinbeck won 25-13, 18-25, 25-19, 25-22, as the Rockets wrapped up at 17-11 overall in matches and 50-34 in games.

In the loss, Ar-We-Va senior Emilee Danner recorded 29 kills to surpass the 1,000-kill plateau for her career.

Danner finished the season with 424 kills and concluded her career with 1,025 kills.
